  "prompt": "Mumbai law college?",
  "response": "Mumbai, being one of the largest cities in India, is home to several prestigious law colleges. Here are some notable law colleges in Mumbai:\n\n1. **Government Law College (GLC) Mumbai**: Established in 1855, GLC is one of the oldest law schools in Asia and offers undergraduate and postgraduate legal education.\n\n2. **University of Mumbai - Department of Law**: The University of Mumbai offers law courses through its department of law.\n\n3. **KC Law College**: Affiliated to the University of Mumbai, KC Law College offers 3-year and 5-year law courses.\n\n4. **SVKM's Pravin Gandhi College of Law**: This college is affiliated with Mumbai University and is known for its 5-year integrated BLS LL.B program.\n\n5. **Jitendra Chauhan College of Law (JC College of Law)**: Affiliated with Mumbai University, it offers a 3-year LL.B. program and is part of the Bhavan\u2019s College Campus.\n\n6. **Rizvi Law College**: Another institution affiliated with the University of Mumbai, providing undergraduate legal education.\n\nThese colleges offer various programs such as the three-year LL.B., the five-year integrated B.A. LL.B./B.L.S. LL.B., and postgraduate courses in law. Admission criteria might include entrance exams, merit-based selection, or other criteria as defined by each institution.",
